We should not change the apiObj. If the interface object will be called two times in a row in one runtime, phase.Validate() and then phase.Run(), this will result in unpredictable behavior.

I think we should find another solution. 

It will be straightforward, easy to understand and less error prone if we put all validation logic into validation method and use new executor for validation.

Something like this:
// Validate makes sure that phase is properly configured
func (p *phase) Validate() error {
	// Check that associated executor if properly configured
	executor, err := p.Executor()
	if err != nil {
		return err
	}
	if err = executor.Validate(); err != nil {
		return err
	}

	buf := bytes.NewBuffer([]byte{})

	if err = executor.Render(buf, ifc.RenderOptions{
		FilterSelector: document.NewSelector()},
	); err != nil {
		return err
	}

	bp := p.helper.PhaseBundleRoot()

	bundle, err := document.NewBundleByPath(bp)

	doc, err := bundle.SelectOne(document.NewSelector().
		ByGvk("airishipit.org", "v1alpha1", "GenericContainer").
		ByName("some-name"))

	factory := p.registry()[schema.GroupVersionKind{
		Group:   doc.GetGroup(),
		Version: doc.GetVersion(),
		Kind:    doc.GetKind(),
	}]

	vaidatorExecutor, err := factory(ifc.ExecutorConfig{
		PhaseName: p.apiObj.Name,
		BundleFactory: func() (document.Bundle, error) {
			return document.NewBundleFromBytes(buf.Bytes())
		},
		ClusterName:      p.apiObj.ClusterName,
		ExecutorDocument: doc,
                ...

	})

	ch := make(chan events.Event)

	go func() {
		vaidatorExecutor.Run(ch, ifc.RunOptions{})
	}()
	return p.processor.Process(ch)
}

Also if you want to save couple of lines of code, we can put kubeconfig creation into separate function.

I think you are modifying Executor() interface signature to satisfy internal implementation logic.

phase.Executor() method, returns an executor for the phase. Here it is not an executor for the phase, it is site wide executor, it is shared between all phases. There can be only single instance of it. 

I don't think that phase interface should return executor based on options. I know this can save couple of lines of code. But this makes interface less intuitive and harder to use. In addition, we should avoid changing interface if we can, and i believe this the case, because this is only needed for internal usage.

There is no use for these options externally. Instead this can be internal implementation.

